-- Script 1
-- How to use
Create a csv file (users-to-modify.csv) and add the users that need to have the email changed. The change will add a “+dummy” to the emails.
* The first column must have the user username, the second column the user current email
* It is possible to modify the script and make it read a column in the csv file with the desired/target email
* Lines 39 to 46 are commented, that part is used to treat the cases where the user is lead of a project or component – in those cases, Jira cannot update the user details if the user is deactivated. If uncommented, the script will activate the users and proceed with the changes

